<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-28"><hi rend="italic">June 28,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 730.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 1434 of the 19th instant, reporting that the claim of Mr. M. Brown
                            on account of his illegal eviction and imprisonment in the City of
                            Mexico has been settled by the payment to him of $10,000.</p>
                        <p>The Department is gratified at the satisfactory adjustment of the
                            claim.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>